1.Types of CSS

(a) Inline CSS
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Inline CSS</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1 style="color: blue; text-align: center;">Hello Inline CSS</h1>
</body>
</html>

(b) Internal CSS

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Internal CSS</title>
  <style>
    h1 {
      color: red;
      text-align: center;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Hello Internal CSS</h1>
</body>
</html>

(c) External CSS

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>External CSS</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Hello External CSS</h1>
</body>
</html>

 create style.css file 
h1 {
  color: green;
  text-align: center;
}



2. Types of CSS Selectors

(a) Universal Selector (*)

* {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

(b) Element Selector

p {
  color: blue;
}


(c) Class Selector (.classname)

.note {
  background-color: yellow;
}

<p class="note">This is a note with yellow background.</p>


(d) ID Selector (#idname)

#special {
  color: red;
  font-weight: bold;
}

<p id="special">This is styled using ID.</p>


(e) Grouping Selector (,)

h1, h2, p {
  text-align: center;
  color: green;
}

(f) Descendant Selector (Parent Child)

div p {
  color: purple;
}

<div>
  <p>This paragraph is inside div</p>
</div>


(g) Child Selector (>)

div > p {
  color: orange;
}


(h) Pseudo-classes

Used for special states (hover, link, visited).

a:hover {
  color: red;
}



(i) Pseudo-elements (::)

Style specific parts of an element.

p::first-letter {
  font-size: 30px;
  color: blue;
}


Final Example: All together

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>CSS Example</title>
  <style>
    * { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; }

    h1 { color: green; }

    .highlight { background: yellow; }

    #unique { color: red; }

    div p { color: blue; }

    a:hover { color: orange; }

    p::first-letter { font-size: 25px; font-weight: bold; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Types of CSS Selectors</h1>
  <p class="highlight">This is class selector example.</p>
  <p id="unique">This is ID selector example.</p>
  <div>
    <p>Paragraph inside div (descendant selector).</p>
  </div>
  <a href="#">Hover me</a>
</body>
</html>













